Cassper Nyovest during the official South African Premiere of Disney's The Lion King at the Johannesburg Country Club on July 18, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Rapper Cassper Nyovest has announced that the next venue for his Fill Up stadium series will be in Rustenburg. In a video posted on Twitter on Monday, Cassper said the concert would be held at the Royal Bafokeng Stadium in the North West Province. READ: Fans slam Cassper Nyovest over twitter comment The Move For Me rapper also addressed gay rumours that were floating around last week. "There is a rumour going around... So basically I just wanted to say, yes, yes I'm gay. Gay means cheerful, gay also means happy... Happy to announce that this years Fill Up is going to Rustenburg", said Cassper. The concert is set to take place on December 15.